//---------------------CLASS------------------------//


What Is a Class (In PHP)?

A class is a blueprint for creating objects and organizing code.

1.A class is simply a container that groups related functions together.
2.These curly braces contain everything inside the class.
3.public function function() This defines a method (function) inside the class.

class HomeController
{
    public function index()
    {
        return "Home page";
    }
}


class Car {
    public function start() {
        return "Car started";
    }
}

web.php =>
Route::get('/home', [HomeController::class, 'index']);



