Blade uses: {{ variable }}
**This prevents security problems like XSS attacks.


//---------------COMMON NAME FOR ROUTES----------//

| Route Name | Purpose             | Example URL     |
| ---------- | ------------------- | --------------- |
| `index`    | show all items      | `/posts`        |
| `show`     | show one item       | `/posts/5`      |
| `create`   | show form to create | `/posts/create` |
| `store`    | save new item       | `/posts`        |
| `edit`     | show edit form      | `/posts/5/edit` |
| `update`   | update item         | `/posts/5`      |
| `destroy`  | delete item         | `/posts/5`      |




//-----------------Blade Layouts (Reusable Page Structure)////////
to avoid repeating main structure in each page see app.blade.php in the view/layouts

| Blade      | Purpose                                   |
| ---------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `@extends` | inherit layout                            |
| `@section` | define content                            |
| `@yield`   | place content in layout                   |
| '@include' | insert a Blade file into anotherBlade file|

example for @include => @include('partials.nav')

---PASSING DATA TO @include---
@include('partials.nav', ['name' => 'Boshra'])

---Difference Between @yield and @include---

| Feature    | Purpose                     |
| ---------- | --------------------------- |
| `@yield`   | placeholder for child views |
| `@include` | insert reusable Blade files |



//-------------Form Validation in Laravel---------------//
| Rule      | Purpose                    |
| --------- | -------------------------- |
| required  | field must exist           |
| email     | valid email format         |
| numeric   | must be a number           |
| min:3     | minimum length             |
| max:50    | maximum length             |
| confirmed | password confirmation      |
| unique    | must be unique in database |




